NEW COMBO OF THE DAY
Doubling up on the left side with thst body, uppercut. OUCH!
Wait for the slow down in middle if video.
TIP👇
You will see me pull back my body slightly between the body and uppercut in slow motion, but in real time you will not see that as much. When you become proficient at boxing the movements are slight but they are there.  The contraction in the core for the slight pull back is there in order to get that left hand out again. But when you are starting out accentuate that pull back of the shoulder more so thst your body can start to understand the mechanics of the movement. Once your shoulders start to relax you will be able to whip out those punches with your core.
Now go practice!!

Sooo, the first year women were allowed to compete in the Olympics, I was training and  cornering Marina at several Olympic Qualifying tournaments around the country. I did not have a Second in the corner with me. Oh, if you don't know what that means, A Second is another coach in the corner helping.
It was just her and I traveling together. It was extremely empowering and such an adventure!
This was before Instagram. We did not have cell phones that could take amazing photos and videos and post them instantly for the world to see. 
But, if I would have been trying to document all of our experiences, I may have actually missed them.
Being present is so important and we are losing the ability to do this every day.
.
.
